{
  "stem": "25639.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They had to live in the outer part of town, right by the cemetery-- well, it's the beginning of town if you come from Beregszasz, or it's the end of town, of course, if you come from the other direction.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And they had to-- they were not permitted to live in-- in the city, and they were not permitted to work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They had a hard time making a living, and they had usually sizable families, and this reduced them to begging.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Jewish people who have-- who have this tremendous history of hardships sympathized with them-- that if they are not permitted to own land, how can they be expected to-- to live?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, it was expected of them to move on from town to town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, the reason they moved on is because they could not put down stakes anywhere, not for long.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were some families, I remember as long back as I can remember my life, and I remember during harvesting period, they would always come, and they always knew that Dad would share the harvest with them.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were also good musicians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is the one thing that they-- one activity that they were permitted to-- to do.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They dressed in very colorful clothing-- usually long, which at that time was seen only on old people, and old people wore dark clothes or-- with white blouses, or this sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But nobody wore colorful clothes as the Gypsies do, and I always loved it on them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Ruffles were usually everywhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was very colorful as they sang their songs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Usually the head of the family played the violin, and the boy children were taught to play the violin.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
